    "body": "### Checked for duplicates?\r\n\r\n- [X] This issue is not a duplicate\r\n\r\n### What are the steps to reproduce this bug?\r\n\r\n1. Connect a gamepad (I have only tested Bluetooth controllers);\r\n2. Make sure you have set controls to answer cards on AnkiDroid's settings;\r\n3. Review a deck: answer with the buttons you have assigned;\r\n4. After the first answer, the whole screen will have a highlight from Android's gamepad UI navigation.\r\n\r\nNOTE: I cannot reproduce this issue with ALL keybindings I set for answering cards, but I tested setting only one button and also setting multiple buttons. Sometimes, reassigning them will cause another keybinding to cause the issue.\r\nI tested face buttons, shoulder buttons, d-pad, and start, in different order of assignments. I couldn't find the steps to reproduce the issue with a particular button, but at least one of them will cause this issue; from my experience, this happens a lot with the d-pad and face buttons.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nA new card should appear without highlighting from gamepad's UI navigation.\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nA new card appears, but the screen is highlighted as a UI element.\r\n\r\n### Debug info\r\n\r\n```text\r\nAnkiDroid Version = 2.16.0beta5\r\n\r\nAndroid Version = 13\r\n\r\nProductFlavor = play\r\n\r\nManufacturer = motorola\r\n\r\nModel = motorola edge 30\r\n\r\nHardware = qcom\r\n\r\nWebview User Agent = Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; Android 13; motorola edge 30 Build/T1RDS33.116-33-3-2; wv) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Chrome/114.0.5735.196 Mobile Safari/537.36\r\n\r\nACRA UUID = 69ebb9c6-295d-4aa8-9fda-2bca62a28367\r\n\r\nNew schema = true\r\n\r\nScheduler = std3\r\n\r\nCrash Reports Enabled = true\r\n\r\nDatabaseV2 Enabled = true\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### (Optional) Anything else you want to share?\r\n\r\nVideo showcasing the issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ankidroid/Anki-Android/assets/27153776/afdf99d4-60e2-4c8f-8b91-171f1f571a8d\r\nThis was reproduced using the d-pad down button. This usually happens with face buttons as well (I recently managed to make the A button not trigger this issue).\r\n\r\n### Research\r\n\r\n- [X] I am reporting a bug specific to AnkiDroid (Android app)\r\n- [X] I have checked the [manual](https://ankidroid.org/docs/manual.html) and the [FAQ](https://github.com/ankidroid/Anki-Android/wiki/FAQ) and could not find a solution to my issue\r\n- [X] (Optional) I have confirmed the issue is not resolved in the latest alpha release ([instructions](https://docs.ankidroid.org/manual.html#betaTesting))",
